.so ../bk-macros
.TH "bk sccslog" 1 %E% "\*(BC" "\*(UM"
.SH NAME 
bk sccslog \- list deltas sorted by date across all files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.Bc bk sccslog [\-ADfnpsv] [
.OPTreq \-c dates
.Bc ] [
.OPTreq \-i d
.Bc ] [
.OPTreq \-r r
.B ]
.BKARGS
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
.B sccslog
is used to get a time sorted listing of changes over all of the specified
or implied files.  It is similar to bk prs, with the difference being
that prs respects file boundaries, i.e., lists all changes in a file 
before going on, but sccslog sorts the changes and prints each change
in time order, ignoring file boundaries.  It is useful to go to a 
directory and type:
.DS
bk sccslog -c-1M
.DE
to see what has happened in all of the files there in the last month.
.LP
By default, bk sccslog runs the output through your pager, which can
be controlled with $PAGER.
.SH OPTIONS
.if t .TP .6i
.if n .TP 1i
.B \-A
Select all uncommitted deltas in a file.
.tp
.OPTreq \-c dates
Cut off dates.  See Range Specifications (below) or
._SA range 
for details.
.\" Undocumented, internal interface.
.\" .tp
.\" .B \-C
.\" Produce comments for a changeset.
.tp
.B \-D
factor out duplicate comments and print the results as
.DS
libdiff.c, gnupatch.c:
  add --minimal to calls to diff(1).
.DE
.tp
.OPTreq \-d dspec
Format output according to the data specification string.  See
bk prs documentation for information on data specifications.
.tp
.B \-f
print the changes in forwards order (oldest to newest).  The
default is backwards order.
.\" Undocumented, internal interface.
.\" .tp
.\" .OPTreq \-i d
.\" Indent output by 
.\" .ARG d
.\" spaces.
.tp
.B \-n
add  a newline to each printed record (sometimes useful with -d).
.tp
.B \-p
Show basenames instead of full pathnames.
.tp
.OPTreq \-r r
Specify a revision or a range.
.tp
.B \-s
produce sorted output for post processing in ``filename|rev'' format.
.tp
.B \-v
Be verbose about errors and processing.
.LP
Note that
.ARG date
may be a symbol, which implies the date of the delta which matches the symbol.
.LP
Range or date specifications:
.if t .TP 1.2i
.if n .TP 1.5i
.I \-r+
prints the most recent delta
.tp
.I \-r1.3..1.6
prints all deltas 1.3 through 1.6
.tp
.I \-c9207..92
prints all deltas from July 1 '92 to Dec 31 '92
.tp
.I \-c92..92
prints all deltas from Jan 1 '92 to Dec 31 '92
